 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Newburgh was born about 1200, in Doncaster, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Henry de Brome. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"about 1200–":"umbes 1200–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1220–1267":"1220–1267","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1267":"1267","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","about 1200":"umbes 1200","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1200–":"noin 1200–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1220–1267":"1220–1267","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1267":"1267","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","about 1200":"noin 1200","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1200–":"environ 1200–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1220–1267":"1220–1267","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1267":"1267","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","about 1200":"environ 1200","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Angleterre","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Doncaster, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alice de Newburgh est née environ 1200, à Doncaster, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Henry de Brome. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"about 1200–":"um 1200–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1220–1267":"1220–1267","1200–Female":"1200–Verstorben","1267":"1267","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","about 1200":"